 On 2/28/07, Paul Schlie <schlie@comcast.net> wrote:
 > It's better, however personally it seems that it would be a little better
 > if some room was stolen from the both the new programming language display
 > and the previously existing line/column display areas (at least with the
 > fonts I use).
 
 It turns out that the line/column display was actually font-sensitive,
 but it didn't have the possibility of growth, so it was
 (conseratively) overly large.
 
 I've changed it to have a more reasonable default, but also the
 ability to grow. Hopefully that works better now.
 
 Narrow enough now, you think?
 
 Robby
